		<div class="styleguide-annotation">
			<h1>Form Fields</h1>
			<dl>
				<dt><a name="theming"></a>Theming</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Theming in Magic Beans is a very simple process. All &quot;themes&quot; are defined in <b>cloud/_variables.scss</b> within each respective object map. The objects include, but are not limited to: input, radio, checkbox, button, calendar, and scrollbar.</p>
					<p>To theme an element, start by adding the CSS class that matches the object you wish to theme (exception: textarea, which uses the same &quot;input&quot; class), i.e. <b>&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; class=&quot;input&quot;</b></p>
					<p>To style with a defined theme, also apply the CSS class <b>&lt;type&gt;-&lt;theme&gt;</b>, where &lt;theme&gt; is the name of the theme defined within the <b>$&lt;type&gt;s</b> (inputs, radios, buttons, scrollbars, etc...) variable in _variables.scss (primary, secondary, etc...)</p>
					<p>For input fields with embedded icons, use the CSS classes <b>icon-left</b> and <b>icon-right</b> in conjunction with a specific <b>icon-&lt;icon&gt;</b> class, where &lt;icon&gt; is the name of the icon you wish to include. Note that icon specific classes are not created dynamically, and must be defined in the cloud/_icon.scss file.</p>
				</dd>
				<br />
				<dt>Input Options</dt>
				<dd>
					<p><b>data-mask=&quot;&lt;mask&gt;&quot;</b> Apply a mask to the input field. Use the number 0 in place of numbers, all other characters are treated literally and will be injected/removed as needed when typing.</p>
					<p><b>data-numeric=&quot;true&quot;</b> Ensure that only numeric characters can be entered.</p>
					<p><b>data-negative=&quot;true&quot;</b> Use in conjunction with numeric option to allow negative numbers to be entered.</p>
					<p><b>data-decimal=&quot;true&quot;</b> Use in conjunction with numeric option to allow decimal numbers to be entered.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Select Options</dt>
				<dd>
					<p><b>data-search=&quot;true/false&quot;</b> Allows/disallows search in &quot;select&quot; dropdowns.</p>
					<p><b>data-search-placeholder=&quot;&lt;text&gt;&quot;</b> Sets the placeholder text of the select search box to the value of &lt;text&gt;.</p>
					<p><b>data-behavior=&quot;&lt;type&gt;&quot;</b> Configures element to behave as if it is whatever the value of &lt;type&gt; is. For now, only the value &quot;input&quot; is supported, which is essentially a text input with a predefined set of options that show on focus.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Calendar Options</dt>
				<dd>
					<p><b>data-date=&quot;true/start/end&quot;</b> Configures input to be a date only field. Focusing on the field will yield the date picker(s). If value is "true", field will behave a single date picker. If value is "start", the field will behave as a date range picker and attempt to locate an end input field (in the order listed) by either using the CSS selector found in the value of <b>data-end</b> attribute of iteself or looking for a following element with the attribute <b>data-date=&quot;end&quot;</b></p>
					<p><b>data-format=&quot;&lt;format&gt;&quot;</b> <span class="styleguide-doc-default">Default: dddd, MMM Do YYYY</span> Specifies the format of rendered dates in input fields, as well as defining the format that existing dates <span class="styleguide-doc-italic">should</span> match in order to be parsed by the underlying date handler framework, momentJS. For consistency and reliability, it is encouraged to use the <b>data-iso8601</b> attribute to provide existing dates, and use this field strictly to define the format of output dates. See below for more information.</p>
					<p><b>data-iso8601=&quot;&lt;ISO-8601 Formatted Date/Time&gt;&quot;</b> Strongly recommended that existing dates be output as the value of this attribute in the standardized iso-8601 format. Outputted dates will still conform to the defined <b>data-format</b> (or default) value above.</p>
					<p><b>data-time=&quot;true&quot;</b> Includes a time picker on each calendar.</p>
					<p><b>data-increment=&quot;&lt;increment&gt;&quot;</b> <span class="styleguide-doc-default">Default: 30</span> Set the increment value in the time picker drop down, in minutes. Also controls how much the time will increase/decrease when the up/down arrows are pressed while focused.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Textarea Options</dt>
				<dd>
					<p><b>data-editable=&lt;theme&gt;</b> On textarea inputs only, given a &lt;theme&gt; name, will convert the field to a rich text formattable field using the Tinymce theme specified. The theme files should be accesible within the /assets/&lt;theme&gt;/ directory. The default theme name is &quot;lightgray&quot;</p>
					<p>See <a href="http://skin.tinymce.com/" target="_blank">http://skin.tinymce.com/</a> to create WYSIWYG editor skins.</p>
					<p><b>data-toolbar=&quot;&lt;toolbar&gt;&quot;</b> Used in conjunction with <b>data-editable</b> to specify a space delimeted list of toolbar buttons on the editor, in the order listed. If not specified, the default buttons are [bold italic underline] in that order. Note that some buttons require the corresponding plugin also be loaded For that, see <b>data-plugins</b></p>
					<p><b>data-plugins=&quot;&lt;toolbar&gt;&quot;</b> Used in conjunction with <b>data-toolbar</b> to specify a list of plugins that should also be loaded to add additional functionality to the editor.</p>
					<p><b>data-position=&quot;top|bottom&quot;</b> The location of the toolbar within the text editor. Defaults to top if not specified.</p>
					<p><b>data-autogrow=&quot;true&quot;</b> If specified, the textarea input will grow as the length of text within it grows. Does not work with <b>data-editable</b> fields.</p>
				</dd>
			</dl>
		</div>
	</div>

