					<p>Tooltips are an easy way to display smaller bits of information when a given element is hovered over. Due to the fact that tooltips rely on markup being injected into a given element, any self closing element (i.e. &lt;input /&gt;) must be wrapped in another element, such as a div/span tag, and the tooltip applied to that element.</p>
